  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The UKPDS risk score is recommended to assess global risk for future coronary heart disease
      (CHD) events in primary prevention. Recently, high-sensitivity C-reactive protein (hsCRP) has
      emerged as a strong independent risk factor for CHD. 18F-fluorodeoxyglucose (FDG) positron
      emission tomography (PET) is a promising imaging technique for the evaluation of vascular
      inflammation that reflects vulnerable atherosclerotic plaque.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
